<body>
    This tools is merely automatizing the tedious parts of 
    <a href="https://thebestoftimes.moddinglinked.com/intro.html">The Best of Times</a>. It does not replace them. For troubleshooting, refers to them.  <br>
     <br>
    <br>
    <b>Requirements</b> 
    <br>
    - A Steam library <b>NOT</b> located in Documents or in Program Files  <br>
    - A non potato gaming computer   <br>
    - Latest Video Driver  <br>
    <br>
    - <a href="/startdownload/VCRedist"><button>All the VSC redistribuable</button></a> Click the button to download them. Then, Run as administrator the "RUN ME AS ADMINISTRATOR LATER.bat" file at the root of this project.

    <br>
    <br>
    <br>
        <b>Manual Steps</b> 
    <br>
    - Install Fallout New Vegas somewhere <b>NOT</b> in Documents/Desktop/Program Files <br>
    - Install Fallout 3 Goty somewhere <b>NOT</b> in Documents/Desktop/Program Files but <b>IN THE SAME DRIVE</b> as Fallout New Vegas<br>
    - Move this project on the same drive as those two installations if it was not the case already <br>
<br>
    - Launch Fallout 3 Goty  at least once  at least once and in the launcher options make sure that everything is maxed, including screen definition and that the correct graphic card is selected. If its not, check power options for software on your laptop.<br>
    - Launch Fallout New Vegas at least once  at least once and in the launcher options make sure that everything is maxed, including screen definition and that the correct graphic card is selected. If its not, check power options for software on your laptop.<br>

    - Make sure you can reach Fallout New Vegas main menu and create a new game. Do not save/play yet.    <br>
    <br> - Copy paste the path of your Fallout New Vegas installation here
    <script>
        let nvpath = "";
        let setNvPath = function(){
            nvpath = document.getElementById("nvpathinput").value;
            console.log(nvpath);
            location.href="/setnvpath?nvpath=" + encodeURIComponent(nvpath);
        }
    </script>
    <br>
    <input type="text" name="nvpath" id="nvpathinput" size="88" value="<%= options.nvpath %>" placeholder="C:\Steam\steamapps\common\Fallout New Vegas"> <button onclick="setNvPath()">SET</button>
    <br><br>

    - Get your Nexus Mod API key from <a href="https://next.nexusmods.com/settings/api-keys" target="_blank">Here</a> and then paste it in the box below. Downloads wont work without one.<br>

    
    <script>
        let nexusapikey = "";
        let setNexusapikey = function(){
            nexusapikey = document.getElementById("nexusapikeyinput").value;
            console.log(nexusapikey);
            location.href="/setnexusapikey?nexusapikey=" + encodeURIComponent(nexusapikey);
        }
    </script>
    <input type="text" name="nexusapikey" id="nexusapikeyinput" size="88" value="<%= options.nexusapikey %>" placeholder=""> <button onclick="setNexusapikey()">SET</button>

    <br><br>
    <b>Mod Organizer</b><br>
    <a href="/startdownload/MO"><button>Download Mod Organizer</button></a> 
    <a href="/execute/MOInstall"><button>Install Mod Organizer</button></a> 

   <br>- Accept the license, click Next.
   <br>- Install it on the same drive as Fallout new vegas. Copy paste the installation path below. <br>
      
    <script>
        let mopath = "";
        let setmopath = function(){
            mopath = document.getElementById("mopathinput").value;
            console.log(mopath);
            location.href="/setmopath?mopath=" + encodeURIComponent(mopath);
        }
    </script>
    <input type="text" name="mopath" id="mopathinput" size="88" value="<%= options.mopath %>" placeholder="C:\TTW\MO2"> <button onclick="setmopath()">SET</button>
    <br>
    - Once the installation is complete, ensure that Launch Mod Organizer is ticked and click Finish.
    <br>
    - Once in mode organizer, click next => Create a Portable Instance => next => Tale of Two Wasteland => Steam => next => Enable All Options => next => leave lcoation to default => next  => finish => clear the read only flag => yes
    <br>
    - You can decide to connect MO2 to nexus in Settings (ctrl s) but it should not be necessary with this tool.
    <br>
    - Launch the fallout launcher from MO2 once and make sure your options are correct (Resolution, details to max, etc...)      <br>
    - Close MO2

     <br><br>
    <b>TTW Core Mod</b><br>
